TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gande, Amar
AU  - Puri, Manju
AU  - Saunders, Anthony
AU  - Walter, Ingo
T1  - Bank Underwriting of Debt Securities: Modern Evidence
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/10.4.1175
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 1175
EP  - 1202
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article examines debt securities underwritten by Section 20 subsidiaries of bank holding companies relative to those underwritten by investment houses. Consistent with a net certification effect for banks, bank underwriting of lower credit rated firms to whom the bank lends results in relatively higher prices (lower yields). We find no evidence of conflicts of interest even when an issue is used to repay bank debt. Further, banks bring a relatively larger proportion of small issues to the market. Contrary to the contention that universal banking stunts availability of finance to small firms, bank underwritings appear to benefit small firms.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/10.4.1175
ER  - 



