TY  - JOUR
AU  - Detemple, Jerome
AU  - Murthy, Shashidhar
T1  - Equilibrium Asset Prices and No-Arbitrage with Portfolio Constraints
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/10.4.1133
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 1133
EP  - 1174
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine intertemporal asset pricing when short sales are constrained in proportion to the value of an investor’s portfolio. All assets’ prices exceed every investor’s marginal utility of consumption-based valuation of the associated dividends if every investor finds himself constrained in some asset in some state; we exhibit such an equilibrium. An asset’s price decomposes into three (investor-specific) components: the consumption value of its dividends, a speculative value premium, and a collateral value premium. The validity of the no-arbitrage pricing approach is shown to depend critically on the difference between real securities and their synthetic counterparts.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/10.4.1133
ER  - 



